  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Space Based Cocoa Certification</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The global demand for sustainable (certified) cocoa is growing annually by 2 to 3%. C&#xF4;te d&#x2019;Ivoire is with 33% of the world&#x2019;s global cocoa production the number one producing country and plays a crucial role in attempts to keep supply up to the growing demand. Of all the produced cocoa in 2015 in C&#xF4;te d&#x2019;Ivoire, 29% was UTZ certified, which makes it the biggest sustainability program and label in the country. UTZ uses its Code of Conduct consisting of control points to check if farmers are compliant to the certificate. Currently, random farmers are audited by people in the field. With satellite imagery, areas can be detected where farmers are expected not comply to the certificate. In that way, non-conformances can better be found, which means that the credibility of the certificate will increase. This pilot project will demonstrate the feasibility of this system.</narrative>
  </description>
